   "id": "db1ecb39-04ce-4370-8ae6-5395822423b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Background Information\n",
    "\n",
    "A regular strictly convex polygon is a polygon that has the following characteristics\n",
    "- all interior angles are less than 180 degrees\n",
    "- all sides have equal length\n",
    "\n",
    "Vertex: The connections between the edges (side).\n",
    "Interior Angles: Angles inside, they are the same.\n",
    "Apothem: Distance between center and midpoint of an edge\n",
    "Circumscribing Circle: Circle that circumscribes polygon and goes through all vertex\n",
    "Circumradius: Radius of the circumscribing circle\n",
    "\n",
    "For a regular strictly convex polygon with\n",
    "- n edges (= n vertices)\n",
    "- R circumradius\n",
    "- s edge\n",
    "- a apothem\n",
    "\n",
    "interior angle = (n - 1) x 180/n\n",
    "s = 2R sin(pi/n)\n",
    "a = R cos (pi/n)\n",
    "perimeter = n*s"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b6464264-c43c-49ad-bf5d-4c6f0255e5d8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Goal 1:\n",
    "\n",
    "Create a Polygon class\n",
    "\n",
    "Initializer\n",
    "- number of edges/vertices\n",
    "- circumradius\n",
    "\n",
    "Properties\n",
    "- edges\n",
    "- vertices\n",
    "- interior angles (calculated)\n",
    "- edge length (calculated)\n",
    "- apothem (calculated)\n",
    "- perimeter (calculated)\n",
    "\n",
    "Functionality\n",
    "- a proper representation (__repr__)\n",
    "- implements equality (==) based on # of vertices and circumradius (__eq__)\n",
    "- implements > based on number of vertices only (__gt__)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d980a95c-2daa-428c-b989-90b22cb173de",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Goal 2:\n",
    "\n",
    "Implement a Polygon sequence type:\n",
    "\n",
    "Initializer\n",
    "- number of vertices for largest polygon in sequence\n",
    "- common circumradius for all polygons\n",
    "\n",
    "Properties\n",
    "- max efficiency polygon: returns the Polygon with the highest area:perimeter ratio\n",
    "\n",
    "Functionality\n",
    "- functions as a sequence type (__getitem__)\n",
    "- supports the len() function (__len__)"
   ]
  },
